se without the financial resources is a concern.[/dropcap]\r\n[/span4]\r\n[span4]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As a semi-technical professional working within the internet/technology industry, I quickly realized that to truly be effective in this field, I needed to learn programming. Not just hack some code-- I mean truly understand the underlying theory, components, and frameworks of computer science. As I explored formal educational options, I was shocked and outraged at the prices. Education used to be an investment. You were granted access to knowledge and a network for a monetary cost. It was usually a good investment-- you would gain skills you could apply.</p>\r\n[/span4]\r\n[span4]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With a looming student loan bubble and an unlimited amount of free, quality resources, it doesn\'t seem to make sense to fork over hard-earned money for what I can find online and in books. This blog is my attempt to uncover the hundreds of free and low-cost alternatives, and to prove that autodidactism can foster skills and talent equal to thousands of dollars and years spent in universities. The joy of learning should not be limited to those with resources, and I am here to prove that.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">- Jacob J. Zhang</p>\r\n[/span4]\r\n[/row_fluid][/widerow]\r\n\r\n[widerow customclass=\"\"][row_fluid]\r\n\r\n[heading_entrance title=\"How I\'m Learning\" text=\"These are the free or low-cost alternatives to formal education that I am using right now to learn software engineering.\"]\r\n\r\n[/row_fluid]\r\n\r\n[row_fluid]\r\n\r\n[span4]\r\n\r\n[skills value=\"50\" size=\"200\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" fgcolor=\"#222222\" donutwidth=\"8\" title=\"MOOCs\" fontsize=\"32px\"]\r\n\r\n[/span4]\r\n\r\n[span4]\r\n\r\n[skills value=\"25\" size=\"200\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" fgcolor=\"#222222\" donutwidth=\"8\" title=\"Books\" fontsize=\"32px\"]\r\n\r\n[/span4]\r\n\r\n[span4]\r\n\r\n[skills value=\"25\" size=\"200\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" fgcolor=\"#222222\" donutwidth=\"8\" title=\"On the Job\" fontsize=\"32px\"]\r\n\r\n[/span4]\r\n\r\n[/row_fluid]\r\n\r\n[/widerow]','About Ship or Deliver','','private','open','open','','about-us','','','2015-05-25 23:50:05','2015-05-25 23:50:05','',0,'http://www.mixmulti.nazwa.pl/hercules-design/?page_id=588',0,'page','',0),(778,2,'2013-06-11 12:36:02','2013-06-11 11:36:02','<ul>\r\n	<li>12 apps w/ Mackenzie Child</li>\r\n	<li>4 Android Apps</li>\r\n	<li>Laravel app - DSCMA form</li>\r\n</ul>','Portfolio','','publish','open','open','zhangportfolio','portfolio','','','2015-12-27 14:23:05','2015-12-27 14:23:05','',0,'http://www.mixmulti.nazwa.pl/hercules-design/?page_id=778',0,'page','',0),(940,2,'2013-06-17 19:03:46','2013-06-17 18:03:46','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Pellentesque quis odio lorem. Vestibulum in hendrerit velit. Sed sed sapien purus, id dapibus elit. Nullam sit amet enim facilisis nisi commodo congue. Integer faucibus dignissim ante, vitae tincidunt libero pretium sed.','FAQ with Categories','','publish','open','open','','faq','','','2013-06-17 19:03:46','2013-06-17 18:03:46','',1037,'http://www.mixmulti.nazwa.pl/hercules-design/?page_id=940',0,'page','',0),(944,2,'2013-06-17 19:20:23','2013-06-17 18:20:23','The Loop is PHP code used by WordPress to display posts. Using The Loop, WordPress processes each post to be displayed on the current page, and formats it according to how it matches specified criteria within The Loop tags. Any HTML or PHP code in the Loop will be processed on each post.\n\nWhen WordPress documentation says \"This tag must be within The Loop\", such as for specific Template Tag or plugins, the tag will be repeated for each post. For example, The Loop displays the following information by default for each post:\n\nYou can display other information about each post using the appropriate <a title=\"Template Tags\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Template_Tags\">Template Tags</a> or (for advanced users) by accessing the variable, which is set with the current post\'s information while The Loop is running.','What is The WordPress Loop?','','publish','closed','closed','','what-is-the-wordpress-loop','','','2013-06-17 19:20:23','2013-06-17 18:20:23','',0,'http://www.mixmulti.nazwa.pl/hercules-design/?post_type=faq&amp;p=944',0,'faq','',0),(945,2,'2013-06-17 19:21:35','2013-06-17 18:21:35','WordPress is open source web software that you can install on your web server to create your website, blog, community or network. WordPress started out as a tool for blogging, but has evolved into a full-fledged Content Management System (CMS), capable of powering websites, networks and communities.','What is WordPress?','','publish','closed','closed','','what-is-wordpress','','','2013-06-17 19:21:35','2013-06-17 18:21:35','',0,'http://www.mixmulti.nazwa.pl/hercules-design/?post_type=faq&amp;p=945',0,'faq','',0),(946,2,'2013-06-17 19:21:54','2013-06-17 18:21:54','One of the principle advantages of WordPress is that you are in control. Unlike remote-hosted scripts such as <a title=\"http://www.blogger.com\" href=\"http://www.blogger.com\">Blogger</a> and <a title=\"http://www.livejournal.com\" href=\"http://www.livejournal.com\">LiveJournal</a>, you host WordPress on your own server. Installation is very simple, as is the configuration. Unlike other software programs, there are not a million files to <a title=\"Changing File Permissions\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Changing_File_Permissions\">chmod</a> nor are there dozens of <a title=\"Templates\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Templates\">templates</a> to edit just to get your site set up and looking the way you want.\n\nAlso, <a title=\"Glossary\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#Blogging\">Blog</a> pages in WordPress are generated on the fly whenever a page is requested, so you do not have multiple archive pages clogging up your web space. Waiting for pages to rebuild is a thing of the past because template changes are made in scant seconds.\n\nWordPress is built following <a title=\"http://www.w3.org/\" href=\"http://www.w3.org/\">W3C</a> standards for <a title=\"Glossary\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#XHTML\">XHTML</a> and <a title=\"Glossary\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#CSS\">CSS</a>, ensuring that your site is more easily rendered across standards-compliant browsers. Other browsers are supported with a few hacks; it’s a reality of the web that hacks are necessary.\n\n<a title=\"Glossary\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#News_reader\">Aggregator</a> support is built-in with a number of standard <a title=\"Glossary\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#RSS\">RSS</a> configurations already done for you, as well as <a title=\"Glossary\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#Atom\">Atom</a>. Following standards makes your WordPress site easier to manage, increases its longevity for future Internet technology adoption, and helps give your site the widest audience possible.','Why Choose WordPress?','','publish','closed','closed','','why-choose-wordpress','','','2013-06-17 19:21:54','2013-06-17 18:21:54','',0,'http://www.mixmulti.nazwa.pl/hercules-design/?post_type=faq&amp;p=946',0,'faq','',0),(947,2,'2013-06-17 19:22:23','2013-06-17 18:22:23','WordPress was primarily inspired by <a title=\"http://www.noahgrey.com/\" href=\"http://www.noahgrey.com/\">Noah Grey</a>\'s <a title=\"http://www.noahgrey.com/greysoft/\" href=\"http://www.noahgrey.com/greysoft/\">Greymatter</a> open-source web log and journal software. It is related to <a title=\"http://cafelog.com/\" href=\"http://cafelog.com/\">b2</a>, sort of a second cousin twice removed. You can use WordPress to post your own stories, ideas, rants, reviews, links, and pictures of your toothless Uncle Ernie at the wedding reception, if you choose. In addition, you can customize the look and feel of your site. Numerous themes are available and may be modified in many different ways. Through the use of <a title=\"Using Themes\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Using_Themes\">WordPress Themes</a>, you can quickly change the look and style of your site. You can also extend WordPress\' functionality through the use of <a title=\"Plugins\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Plugins\">Plugins</a>. Plugins let you create the website or blog that suits your needs. As you can see, its functionality exceeds or at least is similar to what is available in most blogging tools today.','How Is WordPress related to other blogging applications?','','publish','closed','closed','','how-is-wordpress-related-to-other-blogging-applications','','','2013-06-17 19:22:23','2013-06-17 18:22:23','',0,'http://www.mixmulti.nazwa.pl/hercules-design/?post_type=faq&amp;p=947',0,'faq','',0),(948,2,'2013-06-17 19:23:07','2013-06-17 18:23:07','No. You should be able to use WordPress through the user interface, without ever having to touch PHP.\n\nThe only time you would modify your WordPress website with <a title=\"Glossary\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#PHP\">PHP</a> would be when integrating some of the <a title=\"Plugins\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Plugins\">plugins</a>. There are a small number of plugins that still require manual edits to your files. In most cases, clear instructions are usually given within a text file with the <a title=\"Plugins\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Plugins\">plugin</a>.\n\nOther than that, you would not be changing any of the <a title=\"Glossary\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#PHP\">PHP</a> files.','Do I need to know PHP to use WordPress?','','publish','closed','closed','','do-i-need-to-know-php-to-use-wordpress','','','2013-06-17 19:23:07','2013-06-17 18:23:07','',0,'http://www.mixmulti.nazwa.pl/hercules-design/?post_type=faq&amp;p=948',0,'faq','',0),(949,2,'2013-06-16 19:23:28','2013-06-16 19:23:28','The WordPress Codex has a <a title=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary\" href=\"http://code