\'s often too many rules to follow with a high cost.</li>\r\n	<li>RUP had 4 phases: 1) inception, 2) elaboration, 3) construction, and 4) transition. Unfortunately, tools are expensive and are only good for medium to large sizes.</li>\r\n	<li>To avoid needing a strong project manager or simply \"hacking\", the Agile Manifesto (2001) was written. XP version involves extremely short iterations, simplicity, writing test code prematurely, and programming in pairs. The Agile lifecycle is best for SaaS, but not so much for NASA or code subject to regulations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Introduction to Ruby</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li></li>\r\n</ul>','BerkeleyX: Engineering SaaS, Wk 1, Agile & Ruby Intro Notes','','draft','open','open','','','','','2015-03-16 13:57:20','2015-03-16 13:57:20','',0,'http://shipordeliver.com/?p=3028',0,'post','',0),(3029,1,'2015-03-16 13:04:49','2015-03-16 13:04:49','<ul>\r\n	<li>Drawing from traditional engineering, software engineering has a plan-and-document portion to measure progress against.</li>\r\n	<li>First developmental process was waterfall: 1) requirements analysis &amp; specification, 2) architectural design, 3) implementation &amp; integration, 4) verification, and 5) operation and maintenance. Usually when customers see it, they will want changes to the software product, and will realize the right way to do it.</li>\r\n	<li>The spiral lifecycle was next, with a circular iterations. However, they could take 6 to 24 month long, and there\'s often too many rules to follow with a high cost.</li>\r\n	<li>RUP had 4 phases: 1) inception, 2) elaboration, 3) construction, and 4) transition. Unfortunately, tools are expensive and are only good for medium to large sizes.</li>\r\n	<li>To avoid needing a strong project manager or simply \"hacking\", the Agile Manifesto (2001) was written. XP version involves extremely short iterations, simplicity, writing test code prematurely, and programming in pairs.</li>\r\n</ul>','BerkeleyX: Engineering SaaS, Wk 1, Ag